# Course Materials & Lesson Display Modes

Add course-level downloadable materials (PDF, Word, slides, video files) and per-lesson display mode choice (narration script, slide visual, or both) — all **frontend-only with mock/hardcoded data**.

## Proposed Changes

### Course Materials — Types & Data

#### [MODIFY] [types.ts](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/admin/course-content/types.ts)
- Add `CourseMaterial` interface: `{ id, name, type: "pdf"|"word"|"slides"|"video"|"other", size, url }`
- This type will be used in both admin and student views

#### [MODIFY] [courseContent.ts](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/data/courseContent.ts) 
- Add `materials?: CourseMaterial[]` to [CourseContent](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/data/courseContent.ts#97-106) interface
- Add sample mock materials to the existing `medicalSpanishCourse` (e.g., 2-3 mock PDFs, a slide deck)

---

### Course Materials — Admin UI

#### [MODIFY] [course-management/page.tsx](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/admin/course-management/page.tsx)
- Add a **"Materials"** section inside the Add/Edit course modal (below existing fields)
- Provide an "Add Material" button that creates a mock entry with:
  - Name input
  - File type selector (PDF / Word / Slides / Video)
  - A fake "Upload" button (stores mock URL)
- Show the list of attached materials with delete option
- Add `materials` field to the [CourseForm](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/admin/course-management/page.tsx#47-64) interface and `emptyForm`

---

### Lesson Display Mode — Types

#### [MODIFY] [types.ts](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/admin/course-content/types.ts)
- Add `displayMode?: "narration" | "slide" | "both"` to [AdminLesson](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/admin/course-content/types.ts#32-42) type

#### [MODIFY] [courseContent.ts](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/data/courseContent.ts)
- Add `displayMode?: "narration" | "slide" | "both"` to [Slide](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/data/courseContent.ts#53-65) interface
- Set different display modes on a few mock slides for testing (some narration-only, some slide-only, some both)

---

### Lesson Display Mode — Admin UI

#### [MODIFY] [course-content/page.tsx](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/admin/course-content/page.tsx)
- Add a **display mode selector** (3 radio/toggle buttons) to the lesson add/edit form:
  - 📝 **Narration Only** — show narration script
  - 🖼️ **Slide Only** — show visual content/schemas
  - 📝🖼️ **Both** — show narration + slide together (default)
- Persist the choice in `lessonForm` and save it with the lesson data

---

### Lesson Display Mode — Student Player

#### [MODIFY] [learn/page.tsx](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/courses/[id]/learn/page.tsx)
- Update the main lesson view to check `slide.displayMode` (defaulting to `"both"`)
- **`"narration"`**: Show only the [NarrationPanel](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/courses/%5Bid%5D/learn/page.tsx#706-733), hide [SlideContent](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/courses/%5Bid%5D/learn/page.tsx#40-153)
- **`"slide"`**: Show only [SlideContent](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/courses/%5Bid%5D/learn/page.tsx#40-153), hide [NarrationPanel](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/courses/%5Bid%5D/learn/page.tsx#706-733)
- **`"both"`** (default/current): Show both side-by-side (current behavior)
- Add a small toggle button so the student can switch between views even within a lesson

---

### Course Materials — Student View

#### [MODIFY] [learn/page.tsx](file:///c:/DEV/ooskills-frontend/src/app/courses/[id]/learn/page.tsx)
- Add a **"Materials"** tab or collapsible section in the course sidebar
- List all materials with file-type icons (📄 PDF, 📝 Word, 📊 Slides, 🎥 Video)
- Each material has a "Download" link (opens mock URL)

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Admin — Course Materials**: Navigate to `/admin/course-management`, click "Add Course" or "Edit" on an existing course. Scroll down to see the Materials section. Add a material, set name and type, verify it appears in the list. Delete it and verify removal.
2. **Admin — Lesson Display Mode**: Navigate to `/admin/course-content?courseId=<id>`, expand a section, click "Add Lesson" or edit one. Verify the display mode selector appears with 3 options (Narration / Slide / Both).
3. **Student — Display Modes**: Navigate to `/courses/medical-spanish-vocabulary/learn`. Navigate through slides — some should show narration only, some slides only, some both, depending on the mock data.
4. **Student — Materials Panel**: In the learn page, verify the materials section appears in the sidebar with downloadable links.
